✅ 1. Serial console (best for CLI VMs like Alpine)
Connect:
virsh console alpine1

👉 To exit console:

Ctrl + ]
⚠️ If console doesn’t work

Alpine (or your VM) may not have serial console enabled.

Fix inside Alpine (after login via VNC once):

Edit:

vi /etc/inittab

Uncomment or add:

ttyS0::respawn:/sbin/getty -L ttyS0 115200 vt100

Enable kernel console:

Edit:

vi /etc/default/grub

Add:

GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX="console=ttyS0"

Then:

update-grub
reboot
Also ensure VM XML has serial console

From host:

virsh edit alpine1

Make sure this exists:

<console type='pty'>
  <target type='serial' port='0'/>
</console>
